{
  "narration": "The ancient Lost Ward Circle stands before you, its seven weathered monoliths casting long shadows under the flickering glow of the dying blue ward energy. As you step into the clearing's barren earth, the air grows heavy with an unsettling chill. Suddenly, from the mists between the stones, two spectral figures materialize, their ghostly forms swirling with malice and piercing you with cold, empty eyes. Above the center dais, a will-o'-wisp hovers, its eerie light pulsing like a heartbeat of predatory intent. The ward's protective magic may be fading, but these ethereal guardians are vigilant and deadly. The initiative order is established: the second specter strikes swiftly at 14, followed closely by the first specter at 13, then the will-o'-wisp glowing at 8, with you, Norn, moving last at 1. The battle for the fate of the Lost Ward Circle is about to begin. Prepare yourself and tell me, what is your first move? When you are ready to attack, roll a d20 and add your attack bonus.",
  "actions": []
}

{
  "narration": "The second specter moves first, its ghostly form swirling as it lunges at you with a chilling life drain attack. It rolls a d20... a 20! That's a critical hit! Rolling damage, doubling damage dice for the critical strike: it rolls 3d6 and 3d6 for the necrotic life drain, getting 2, 7, 3 plus 2, 7, 3, total 24 necrotic damage! The cold drains into your very soul, sapping your vitality. You feel your strength falter as the specter attempts to steal your life energy.\n\nNext, the first specter attacks. It rolls a d20... an 11. Adding its attack bonus +4, total 15. Your armor class is 16, so the attack misses as you deftly evade the creeping grasp.\n\nThe will-o'-wisp flickers erratically, then shoots a bolt of lightning at you. Rolling a d20... 19! Adding the attack bonus +4, total 23, a hit! It rolls damage: 2d8 lightning damage, results 2 and 7, totaling 9 damage searing your flesh with arcs of crackling energy.\n\nNow, Norn, it's your turn. You have taken 33 points of damage from the specter's critical life drain and the will-o'-wisp's lightning shock, but you remain standing. The second specter stares with soulless eyes, ready to strike again. Please roll a d20 for your attack roll and add your attack bonus of +5. Let me know the result when ready.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 24 necrotic damage from the second specter's critical life drain attack and 9 lightning damage from the will-o'-wisp's shock, total 33 damage. Current HP: 29 - 33 = -4, Norn is unconscious."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "The second specter strikes first, its ghostly claws reaching out with a chilling touch. It rolls a d20... a natural 20! With your Improved Critical feature, this is a devastating critical hit. Rolling damage for the life drain attack twice over: 2, 7, 3 and again 2, 7, 3 totals 24 necrotic damage. The coldness unnerves you as your life's energy bleeds away, reducing your hit points from 29 down to 5. The first specter follows swiftly, but its attack roll of 11 plus 4 equals 15, just shy of your armor class of 16, missing its mark.\n\nSuddenly the will-o'-wisp darts forward, unleashing a searing shock of lightning. The attack roll is 19 plus 4, totaling 23, striking true. It deals 9 lightning damage, dragging your HP down from 5 to -4. You collapse to the ground, the dark energy overwhelming your body as you slip unconscious.\n\nYour vision fades as the malevolent energies of the Lost Ward Circle press in. You will need to make death saving throws on your turns to cling to life.\n\nThe round ends with your allies yet to act and enemies ready to continue their assault.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Norn takes 24 necrotic damage from the second specter's critical life drain and 9 lightning damage from the will-o'-wisp's shock, reducing HP from 29 to -4. Norn is now unconscious."
      }
